<subSubSection id="71C172CAFFC2FFB4FF53FA20FD84FEC1" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="183" pageId="2" pageNumber="181" type="description">
<paragraph id="39642141FFC2FFB2FF53FA20FE57F9D4" blockId="2.[166,1225,1412,1855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">R e d e s c r i p t i o n. Measurements (mm): length of antenna: 0.64–0.66; maximal head width (including eyes): 0.44–0.48; head length (the anterior margin of the clypeus to the posterior margin of the head): 0.29–0.34; maximal width of pronotum: 0.48–0.54; length of pronotum (measured along its midline): 0.33–0.38; length of elytra at suture: 0.36–0.39; maximal width of elytra (combined width of each elytron when elytra closed along suture): 0.66–0.79; total length of body (from anterior margin of labrum to posterior margin of tergite VIII): 2.3–2.5.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="39642141FFC2FFB2FF53F9C1FE1AF955" blockId="2.[166,1225,1412,1855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">Coloration: head dark-brown, glossy; pronotum brown, glossy; elytra yellow-brown, posterior angles and base with 2 (1 on each elytron) triangle, apically pointed, dark brown spots; abdomen pale brown, abdominal tergites VI and VII dark brown; mouthparts, antennae and legs yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="39642141FFC2FFB3FF53F941FD37FE82" blockId="2.[166,1225,1412,1855]" lastBlockId="3.[174,1233,175,1098]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="182" pageId="2" pageNumber="181">Head strongly transverse, 1.45–1.38 times as wide as long, vertex with 6 or more sparse, small, round, distinct punctures on each side; microsculpture hardly distinct or absent. Antennae length; antennal segment I long strongly widened towards apex; segment II long, narrower and shorter than segments I; segment III narrower and shorter than segment II; segment IV small and short; segments V-X slightly strongly transverse, 1.33–1.50 times as wide as long, segments each, almost parallel-sided.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="39642141FFC3FFB3FF6BFEB5FCD4FE62" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,1098]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">Pronotum smooth; strongly transverse, 1.42–1.45 times as wide as long and 1.09– 1.13 times as wide as head; posterior angles and posterior margin of pronotal disc rounded; in middle and lateral sides of pronotal disc with sparse, scattered, small, rounded punctures, in the middle near anterior margin with 2 longitudinal discontinuous in centre rows, each with 2 moderately large and some small round, distinct punctures, in the middle near posterior margin with 2 large, round punctures, posterior margin with even, dense, small punctation; microsculpture hardly distinct or absent.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="39642141FFC3FFB3FF6BFE4AFC2EFDA1" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,1098]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">Elytra 1.38–1.46 times as wide as pronotum; with dense and small punctuation; microsculpture dense and distinct; with sparsely distributed fine setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="39642141FFC3FFB3FF6BFD8AFD7FFD41" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,1098]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">
Abdomen: abdominal tergites, each, with dense and distinct microsculpture; Male: posterior margin of tergite VII in the middle with 2 large, round striae and lateral some longitudinal, short striae; posterior margin of tergite VII with 1 moderately long, weakly sharpened and curved inwards processes laterally and in the middle with 2 lightly shorter appendages (
<figureCitation id="A1E03DC4FFC3FFB3FECEFD0AFE4BFD42" box="[326,387,687,713]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[169,202,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[241,1137,1151,1650]" captionTargetId="figure-388@3.[236,1141,1147,1651]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Gyrophaena orientalis: 1 — 8th abdominal tergites of male; 2 — aedeagus in lateral view; 3 — aedeagus in dorsal and in lateral view; 1—3 — redrawn (after Ádám, 2008, with amendments)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452916" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452916/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A1E03DC4FFC3FFB3FE06FD0AFE54FD42" box="[398,412,687,713]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1779,1801]" captionTargetBox="[322,1089,1255,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-405@1.[315,1091,1252,1773]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Gyrophaena fusicornis: 1 — 8th abdominal tergites of male; 2 — aedeagus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452914/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC3FFB3FE06FD0AFE54FD42" box="[398,412,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="A1E03DC4FFC3FFB3FDBCFD0AFD42FD42" box="[564,650,687,713]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[169,202,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[241,1137,1151,1650]" captionTargetId="figure-388@3.[236,1141,1147,1651]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Gyrophaena orientalis: 1 — 8th abdominal tergites of male; 2 — aedeagus in lateral view; 3 — aedeagus in dorsal and in lateral view; 1—3 — redrawn (after Ádám, 2008, with amendments)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452916" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452916/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">
fig. 2, 
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC3FFB3FDF4FD0AFD42FD42" box="[636,650,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A1E03DC4FFC3FFB3FD10FD0AFD6EFD42" box="[664,678,687,713]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1785,1807]" captionTargetBox="[317,1080,1212,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-399@4.[308,1084,1209,1768]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Gyrophaena plutenkowi sp. n.: 1 — 8th abdominal tergites of male; 2 — aedeagus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452920/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC3FFB3FD10FD0AFD6EFD42" box="[664,678,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="39642141FFC3FFB3FF6BFD6AFE26FCC2" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,1098]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">
C o m m e n t s. The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="FEDB5AC2FFC3FFB3FD65FD75FC48FD62" authorityName="A. Strand" authorityYear="1938" box="[749,896,719,746]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC3FFB3FD65FD75FC48FD62" box="[749,896,719,746]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">G. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on an unspecified number of 
<typeStatus id="E6609FE3FFC3FFB3FEBDFD55FE52FC81" box="[309,410,752,778]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">syntypes</typeStatus>
collected “Sistikem Sibir” collected by “Fritz Jansen” (
<bibRefCitation id="5D4A5CB0FFC3FFB3FBAFFD4AFB0CFC81" author="Strand, A." box="[1063,1220,751,778]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" pagination="39 - 40" refId="ref4388" refString="Strand, A. Gyrophaena orientalis n. sp. (Col., Staph.) // Notulae Entomologicae. - 1938. - 18. - P. 39 - 40." type="book chapter" year="1938">Strand, 1938</bibRefCitation>
). A male 
<typeStatus id="E6609FE3FFC3FFB3FE99FCB5FEA4FCA1" box="[273,364,784,810]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">syntype</typeStatus>
<materialsCitation id="89B32B1CFFC3FFB3FEFEFCB5FE23FCC2" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3751757303" collectionCode="NHMO" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="lectotype">
was located in the collections of the were found at the (
<collectionCode id="5FCAB984FFC3FFB3FBA0FCAAFB42FCA1" box="[1064,1162,783,810]" country="Norway" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/2knt-7f1r" name="Natural History Museum, University of Oslo" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" type="Museum">NHMO</collectionCode>
); it is designated as the 
<typeStatus id="E6609FE3FFC3FFB3FEF5FC8AFE23FCC2" box="[381,491,815,841]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">lectotype</typeStatus>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="39642141FFC3FFB4FF6BFCEAFD48FF62" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,1098]" lastBlockId="4.[166,1225,175,330]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="183" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">
The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="FEDB5AC2FFC3FFB3FDAFFCF5FD38FCE2" authorityName="Glotov" authorityYear="2014" box="[551,752,847,874]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transsylvanica">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC3FFB3FDAFFCF5FD38FCE2" box="[551,752,847,874]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">G. transsylvanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a single 
<typeStatus id="E6609FE3FFC3FFB3FC6EFCEAFB85FCE2" box="[998,1101,847,873]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">holotype</typeStatus>
male from 
<collectingCountry id="41CC61D1FFC3FFB3FF26FCCAFED1FC02" box="[174,281,879,905]" name="Romania" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">Romania</collectingCountry>
“Herkulesfürdõ” and 
<specimenCount id="2FDDEAC8FFC3FFB3FDADFCD5FD04FC01" box="[549,716,880,906]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">two paratypes</specimenCount>
(
<specimenCount id="2FDDEAC8FFC3FFB3FD56FCCAFC85FC02" box="[734,845,879,905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount id="2FDDEAC8FFC3FFB3FC05FCD5FBD9FC01" box="[909,1041,879,906]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
) from 
<collectingCountry id="41CC61D1FFC3FFB3FBEFFCD5FB18FC01" box="[1127,1232,880,906]" name="Hungary" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">Hungary</collectingCountry>
“Hu., Bihar, Galbina, Bokor” (
<bibRefCitation id="5D4A5CB0FFC3FFB3FDABFC2AFD75FC21" author="Adam, L." box="[547,701,911,938]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" pagination="153 - 170" refId="ref3901" refString="Adam, L. New species of Aleocharinae from Romania and Croatia (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) // Travaux du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle &quot; Grigore Antipa &quot;. - 2008. - 51. - P. 153 - 170." type="book chapter" year="2008">Ádám, 2008</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="5D4A5CB0FFC3FFB3FD5DFC2AFCBDFC21" author="Adam, L." box="[725,885,911,938]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" pagination="153 - 170" refId="ref3901" refString="Adam, L. New species of Aleocharinae from Romania and Croatia (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) // Travaux du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle &quot; Grigore Antipa &quot;. - 2008. - 51. - P. 153 - 170." type="book chapter" year="2008">Ádám (2008)</bibRefCitation>
compared 
<taxonomicName id="FEDB5AC2FFC3FFB3FB8BFC35FB18FC22" authorityName="Glotov" authorityYear="2014" box="[1027,1232,911,938]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transsylvanica">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC3FFB3FB8BFC35FB18FC22" box="[1027,1232,911,938]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">G. transsylvanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="FEDB5AC2FFC3FFB3FF61FC15FDF8FC42" authority="A. Strand, 1939" authorityName="A. Strand" authorityYear="1939" box="[233,560,943,970]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsi">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC3FFB3FF61FC15FEBDFC42" box="[233,373,943,970]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">G. williamsi</emphasis>
A. Strand, 1939
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FEDB5AC2FFC3FFB3FDE2FC15FC58FC41" authority="Strand, 1935" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1935" box="[618,912,943,970]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munsteri">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC3FFB3FDE2FC15FD3BFC42" box="[618,755,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">G. munsteri</emphasis>
Strand, 1935
</taxonomicName>
, but there was no reference whatsoever to 
<taxonomicName id="FEDB5AC2FFC3FFB3FED7FC75FE38FC62" authorityName="A. Strand" authorityYear="1938" box="[351,496,975,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC3FFB3FED7FC75FE38FC62" box="[351,496,975,1002]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">G. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the figures of the aedeagus of the 
<typeStatus id="E6609FE3FFC3FFB3FC28FC6AFBCFFC62" box="[928,1031,975,1001]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="E6609FE3FFC3FFB3FBC0FC75FB66FC61" box="[1096,1198,976,1002]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="FEDB5AC2FFC3FFB3FF26FC55FEBFFB82" authorityName="Glotov" authorityYear="2014" box="[174,375,1007,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transsylvanica">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC3FFB3FF26FC55FEBFFB82" box="[174,375,1007,1034]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">G. transsylvanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="5D4A5CB0FFC3FFB3FE28FC4AFDF6FB81" author="Adam, L." box="[416,574,1007,1034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" pagination="153 - 170" refId="ref3901" refString="Adam, L. New species of Aleocharinae from Romania and Croatia (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) // Travaux du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle &quot; Grigore Antipa &quot;. - 2008. - 51. - P. 153 - 170." type="book chapter" year="2008">Ádám (2008)</bibRefCitation>
are rather misleading. An examination of the 
<typeStatus id="E6609FE3FFC3FFB3FBE1FC4AFB18FB82" box="[1129,1232,1007,1033]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="E6609FE3FFC3FFB3FF68FBB5FE99FBA1" box="[224,337,1040,1066]" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">paratypes</typeStatus>
revealed that it is identical to 
<taxonomicName id="FEDB5AC2FFC3FFB3FD24FBB5FCF1FBA2" authorityName="A. Strand" authorityYear="1938" box="[684,825,1039,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC3FFB3FD24FBB5FCF1FBA2" box="[684,825,1039,1066]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="182">G. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in external characters, as well as in the shape of the male sternite VIII and in the morphology of the aedeagus. An examination of the 
<typeStatus id="E6609FE3FFC4FFB4FF7FFF0AFE96FF42" box="[247,350,175,201]" pageId="4" pageNumber="183">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="E6609FE3FFC4FFB4FE16FF15FDCCFF41" box="[414,516,176,202]" pageId="4" pageNumber="183">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="FEDB5AC2FFC4FFB4FDB8FF15FD32FF42" authorityName="Glotov" authorityYear="2014" box="[560,762,175,202]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transsylvanica">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC4FFB4FDB8FF15FD32FF42" box="[560,762,175,202]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="183">G. transsylvanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that it refers to 
<taxonomicName id="FEDB5AC2FFC4FFB4FBB9FF15FB09FF42" authorityName="A. Strand" authorityYear="1938" box="[1073,1217,175,202]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="0BAFFD53FFC4FFB4FBB9FF15FB09FF42" box="[1073,1217,175,202]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="183">G. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Hence the synonymy is proposed above.
</paragraph>
<caption id="6DA471C9FFC3FFB3FF21F967FC10F978" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452916" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6452916" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452916/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="182" startId="3.[169,202,1730,1752]" targetBox="[241,1137,1151,1650]" targetPageId="3">
